name: Alternating case
description:
You are given a string consisting of alphabet letters. Convert it to
alternating case: the letters on odd positions should be in uppercase, and the
letters on even positions should be lowercase. The letters are numbered
staring from 1. Input The only line of input contains a string between 1 and
100 characters long. Each character of the string is either an uppercase
('A'-'Z') or a lowercase ('a'-'z') letter. Output Output the resulting string.
Examples Input Codeforces Output CoDeFoRcEs Input VKCup Output VkCuP
